Chapter 7.6: Phonetic Analysis of Sentence Modes

7.6.1.1 Mode-only Models

knitr::opts_chunk$set(warning = F, message = F, tidy = "styler")

# Load Functions.
source("../../2_R_Functions/myFunctions.R")

# Load packages.
installMissingPackages(
  c(
    # Include statistical packages.
    "performance",
    "lmerTest",
    "lme4",
    "optimx",
    "MuMIn",
    # Include packages for tidy output.
    "tidyverse",
    "broomExtra",
    "sjPlot",
    "formattable",
    "knitr",
    "RColorBrewer",
    # Include packages for %in% %notin% syntactic notation
    "mefa4"
  )
)

y_lim_t <- c(0, 360)
y_lim_f0 <- c(-4.1, 10.5)
l_star_h_types <- c("^[L*]H", "L*H", "L*^[H]", "^[L*H]")

# Load Corpus
m_corpus <- get_m_corpus("../../4_data/m_corpus.csv") %>%
  # Select only columns for analysis
  select(
    speaker,
    gender,
    mode,
    prompt,
    acc_phon,
    fin_phon,
    l_t,
    l_f0,
    h_t,
    h_f0
  ) %>%
  filter(acc_phon %in% l_star_h_types) %>%
  mutate(acc_phon = factor(acc_phon,
    levels = l_star_h_types
  ))

A. Low Targets

A.1. l_t model

  • Following intercepts only model for parity with other time parameter models.
  • model needs trimmed (residual SD > 3.5)
# run model
l_t_mode_only_mdl <-
  lmer(l_t ~
    mode
    + gender
    + (1 | speaker)
    + (1 | fin_phon)
    + (1 | prompt),
  data = m_corpus,
  control = lmerControl(
    optimizer = "optimx",
    calc.derivs = F,
    optCtrl = list(
      method = "nlminb",
      starttests = F,
      kkt = F
    )
  )
  )

l_t_mode_only_mdl <- optimizeModel(l_t_mode_only_mdl)

# Model needs trimmed.
l_t_mode_only_mdl <- update(l_t_mode_only_mdl,
  data = m_corpus %>% filter(abs(scale(resid(
    l_t_mode_only_mdl
  ))) <= 3.5)
)

l_t_mode_only_mdl <- optimizeModel(l_t_mode_only_mdl)
write <- "output/l_t_mode_only"

l_t_mode_only.summary <- summariseLME(l_t_mode_only_mdl,
  run_step = F,
  write = paste0(write, "_anova.csv"),
  print_summary = F,
  plot_resids = F
)

Predictions

l_t_mode_only.tidy <- analyseModel(
  l_t_mode_only_mdl,
  write = "output/l_t_mode_only",
  print_r2 = F,
  short_caption = T,
  y_lim = y_lim_t,
  y_lab = "t (ms)",
  caption_suffix = " (mode only model)",
  plot_rounding = 0
)

printTidyPredictions(l_t_mode_only_mdl,
  digits = 0,
  caption_suffix = " (mode only model)"
)

  • model needs trimmed (residual SD > 3)

# as per mode and acc_phon model

  lmer(l_f0 ~
    mode
    + gender
    + (1 | speaker)
    + (1 | fin_phon)
  #+ (1 | prompt)
  ,
  data = m_corpus,
  control = lmerControl(
    optimizer = "optimx",
    calc.derivs = F,
    optCtrl = list(
      method = "nlminb",
      starttests = F,
      kkt = F
    )
  )
  )

l_f0_mode_only_mdl <- optimizeModel(l_f0_mode_only_mdl)

# Model needs trimmed.

  data = m_corpus %>% filter(abs(scale(resid(
    l_f0_mode_only_mdl

# run model
l_t_mode_phon_mdl <-
  lmer(l_t ~
    mode
    + acc_phon
    + gender
    + (1 | speaker)
    + (1 | prompt)
    + (1 | fin_phon),
  data = m_corpus,
  control = lmerControl(
    optimizer = "optimx",
    calc.derivs = F,
    optCtrl = list(
      method = "nlminb",
      starttests = F,
      kkt = F
    )
  )
  )

l_t_mode_phon_mdl <- optimizeModel(l_t_mode_phon_mdl)

# Model needs trimmed.
l_t_mode_phon_mdl <- update(l_t_mode_phon_mdl,
  data = m_corpus %>% filter(abs(scale(resid(
    l_t_mode_phon_mdl
  ))) <= 3.25)
)

)

# Load Corpus
m_corpus <- get_m_corpus("../../4_data/m_corpus.csv") %>%
  # Keep only factors needed for analysis
  select(
    speaker,
    gender,
    mode,
    utt_mean_f0,
    utt_slope,
    phr_phon,
    acc_phon,
    fin_phon,
    prompt
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    # h_start = phrases beginning with a high boundary or H* in first foot.
    h_start = if_else(!is.na((str_extract(phr_phon, "%H|\\^\\[%H|% H\\*"))),
      "H start",
      "no H start"
    ),
    h_start = factor(h_start, levels = c("H start", "no H start")),
    # Remove register tier identifers from fin_phon. (See Chapter 7.5.2.2.)
    fin_phon = factor(str_replace_all(fin_phon, "\\^|\\[|\\]", ""),
      levels = c("%", "L%")
    )
  )
